snippet.textDisplay: How should I describe this song? A heady concoction of love, music, & poetry? A beautiful ode to longing? Or a letter that breaks your heart into a hundred million pieces? It's all of these and more. Thank you very much, Dear Piyush, you dark horse, you rockstar, you poet. Please see to it that your pen never runs dry. For now, we're hungry for more. Also, thanks to each and everyone at Coke Studio for raising the bar really high this time round. Cheers! :)

snippet.textDisplay:
THIS IS IT!!!!

I agree, Saathi Salaam was a great track, but Clinton's English usage was a major put off in few songs in Episode 1

This time they have got everything right! Above all the concept of the show! Cokestudio means bringing those music gems deep rooted in our culture, with a modern twist. The modern orchestration is supposed to enhance the original song, not to overpower it. 

Hitesh Sonilk understands this & here we are - with a BRILLIANT SONG!
